    "created_at": "2017-07-26T15:33:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-07-26T15:33:25Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I confirm the issue.\r\n\r\n`setDefaultRootsPem()` is allocating a memory buffer large enough to contain the roots pem. The memory buffer is never freed. Calling `setDefaultRootsPem()` multiple times will allocate the buffer again, and leak more memory: https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/7897ae9308a25a064ee2e7386da25d37cc3273fa/src/php/ext/grpc/channel_credentials.c#L99\r\n\r\nFrom looking at the code, it seems that other language bindings may suffer from the same issue."
